                <DIV class="ReviewHeading">Book Description:</DIV>
                <span id="Label1"><div><b>National Book Award Nominee</b><br><b>American Library Association Notable Book</b><br><b>An Outstanding Book in Women's History at the Berkshire Conference of Women Historians</b><br><br>From the collapse of the Kaiser's regime to the destruction of Hitler in his bunker, Germany has been studied, explicated, and psychoanalyzed time and again. Yet there have been few detailed investigations into the historical and cultural roles played by German women in modern times. This important book, which <i>Kirkus</i> called "original and intriguing," corrects this imbalance.<br></div></span>
              
